    "2022; Houlsby et al. 2019a; Gong et al.",
    "2024) emerge as the pivotal solution due to their superior parameter-performance trade-off.Existing PEFT methods designed for language or nature imagery have made great progress with excellent works, such as LoRA (Hu et al. 2021), Visual Prompt Tuning (VPT) (Jia et al.",
    "However, most exhibit significant performance degradation in remote sensing (RS) segmentation tasks when integrated with DINOv2 (Oquab et al. 2023) (experimental evidence provided in later sections).",
    "We argue the main reason lies in the influences of artifacts in the features.",
    "As shown in Figure 2 (a), we show the PCA visualization of features of DINOv2-L, which contains obvious redundant artifacts."
  ]
